WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, Jacob. It's Thursday, April second, six A-M in

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Jefferson City. This is the day. Your Anthropic pilot meeting

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
is in three hours. The government's appeal deadline on Anthropic

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
versus the Pentagon is today. Humans are orbiting the moon

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
right now. And Trump told the nation last night he's

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
going to bomb Iran, quote, "back to the Stone Ages."

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Let's get into it. Weather first. Jefferson City: seventy-eight degrees

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
today with thunderstorms, eighty-two percent chance of rain, wind gusts

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
up to forty-one miles per hour. Ugly morning for a

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
big day. Drive carefully. Tacoma: fifty-two degrees, chance of rain,

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
mostly cloudy. Katelyn's off day is gray but manageable. Friday

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
looks better for both of you. Your calendar. Nine A-M:

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
Anthropic pilot discussion. This is the meeting you've been prepping

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
for since March first. Two P-M: Bill Review Training. Six-fifteen

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
P-M: Dinner with Alex, Chris, and Dustin. Dustin texted the

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
group last night asking for a time and place. You

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
still need to respond. And Katelyn is off today —

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
she texted yesterday that she misses you and wishes she

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
could crash on your couch and watch Jeopardy with you

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
tonight. Text messages. Katelyn sent you a sweet message yesterday

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
afternoon — "I miss you too. I wish we could

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
crash and watch Jeopardy together tonight." You'd texted first saying

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
you wished she were there. The long-distance ache is real

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
but the affection is too. Call her after dinner tonight.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
Dustin got his truck back! Finally — it's been almost

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
a month since the accident. He confirmed yesterday and you

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
congratulated him. He also set dinner logistics at six-fifteen tonight,

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
mentioning you, Alex, and Chris. Venue is still T-B-D. Please

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
respond in the group chat. Alex sent a YouTube link

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
and continued the robot vacuum conversation. Ben has no new

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
messages — he's back in K-C. Now, the news. The

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
Anthropic pilot meeting at nine A-M is happening against an

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
extraordinary backdrop. Today is the deadline for the government to

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
appeal Judge Lin's preliminary injunction — the ruling that called

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
banning Anthropic, quote, "classic illegal First Amendment retaliation." Overnight, Axios

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
broke that Democratic congressman Josh Gottheimer wrote to Dario Amodei

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
demanding answers about the Claude Code source leak. The key

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
line: quote, "Claude is a critical part of our national

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
security operations." That's a Democrat defending Claude's importance while pressing

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
on security — and it's exactly the argument you're about

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
to make in a conference room in Jefferson City. Also:

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
Jamie Dimon told Axios he was personally briefed on Anthropic's

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
unreleased Mythos model, calling A-I agents a major cyber risk.

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
The most powerful banker in America is in the Anthropic

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
briefing room. That signals how seriously Wall Street is taking

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
this. Iran, day thirty-four. Trump's prime-time address last night: the

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
U-S will hit Iran, quote, "extremely hard" over the next

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
two to three weeks, bringing them, quote, "back to the

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
Stone Ages." He gave Iran until April sixth to reopen

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
the Strait of Hormuz. Oil immediately spiked six percent. Asian

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
stocks fell. U-S futures plummeted. The U-K is hosting thirty-plus

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
foreign ministers today to discuss a diplomatic solution. China and

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
Pakistan proposed a five-point peace plan. And Europe's far-right parties

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
are breaking with Trump — Marine Le Pen called the

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
strikes catastrophic, Germany's A-F-D demanded U-S troops leave. The international

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
coalition is fracturing. Quick status board. D-H-S shutdown is at

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
day forty-eight — Republican leaders announced a two-track plan to

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
end it, but Congress is on recess until April thirteenth.

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
Space-X filed confidentially for its I-P-O yesterday — one-point-seven-five trillion

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
dollar valuation, June listing, largest I-P-O in history. Artemis two

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
is in lunar transit — launched successfully yesterday, Orion performing

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
beautifully, lunar orbit in four days. Tech and A-I. That

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
Gottheimer letter is the big story. Also: forty-seven percent of

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
college students are reconsidering their majors because of A-I, according

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
to new Gallup polling. Sixteen percent have already changed. The

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
future workforce is reshaping itself around A-I anxiety before A-I

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
has even fully arrived. The Every newsletter covered Linear reinventing

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
itself as an agent-native business — relevant to your pilot

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
meeting thinking about what tools look like when designed for

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
A-I from the ground up. Spending. Your Roborock Saros ten-R

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
robot vacuum shipped from Amazon this morning. The robot vacuum

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
deep-dive with Alex has reached its commercial conclusion. Also shipped:

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
corner shower caddy plus two more items. Rocket Mortgage payment

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
cleared. And Pebble wants you to pick your Index zero-one

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
ring size — don't let that expire. Blind spots. The

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
Iran war is causing a helium shortage. Helium from Gulf

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
gas fields powers M-R-I scanners and A-I chipmaking, and has

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
no good substitutes. India started counting one-point-four-seven billion people today

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
in a census delayed five years. Hungary votes next week

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
with Orban's sixteen-year rule in jeopardy. Action items. Nine A-M:

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
walk into the Anthropic meeting confident. You know the material.

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
Respond to Dustin's group text about dinner. Call Katelyn tonight.

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
Check the City of Seattle job posting directly — it

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
disappeared from Indeed yesterday. Pick your Pebble ring size. Here's

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
the thing about today. Your pilot meeting is at nine.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
The government's appeal deadline is the same day. A congressman

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
just called Claude critical to national security. Jamie Dimon was

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
briefed on Mythos. Four astronauts are heading to the moon.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
And Katelyn is sitting in Tacoma wishing she could watch

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
Jeopardy with you on the couch you just got new

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
carpet for. Somewhere between all of that, you're going to

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
walk into a room and make the case for a

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
technology you believe in. You've prepped for this. Go make

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
it count. And for god's sake, respond to Dustin about

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:18.800
the restaurant. Have a great Thursday, Jacob.
